	<p>The crumbly nature of the florist foam demanded some form of protective shell to encourage handing the prototype. Following three layers of both white primer and nutmeg-colored aerosol, the foam retained its form and no longer crumbles. Roughly sanding a single layer of nutmeg on 5/16" dow mast pieces created a weathered texture; and rolling the candle-stick holder cannons and cannonballs in a black-sprayed cup created a grimy, greasy texture.</p>
